headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 39 points and the Chicago Bulls sent the Detroit Pistons to their franchise-record 67th loss of the season, 127-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chicago beats Detroit 127-105, sending Pistons to franchise-record 67th loss

events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 39 points in three quarters and the New York Knicks kept up their quest to finish with the No. 2 seed in the Eastern Conference by beating the Boston Celtics 118-109 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 39 points, Knicks beat Celtics to keep up push for No. 2 seed in Eastern Conference

headlines.description: — Luka Samanic scored a season-high 22 points to help the Utah Jazz snap a 13-game losing streak with a 124-121 victory over the Houston Rockets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Samanic scores 22, helps Jazz snap 13-game skid with 124-121 win over Rockets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 22 points and the Golden State Warriors rallied down the stretch for a 100-92 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry has 22 points, Warriors rally to beat Trail Blazers 100-92

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum and Zion Williamson each scored 31 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat Sacramento 135-123 on Thursday night to complete a five-game season sweep of the Kings.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Williamson score 31 apiece, Pelicans complete five-game sweep of Kings with 135-123 win
